<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41036a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41036a">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41036a"> 36(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bigamy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A person is guilty of <mark>bigamy</mark>, who, being married, goes through a legally recognised ceremony of marriage with another person, during the life of the former husband or wife, unless the former marriage has been dissolved or declared void, or the accused believes, on reasonable grounds, that the former husband or wife is dead. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 31</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: This page is misplaced as (unnumbered) page 34 in the JJA. </mm> </dd></dl>
